<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>In Zend/Date.php (version 1.10.4) lines 4910 to 4916, the formats for TIME_LONG, TIME_MEDIUM and TIME_SHORT are incorrectly translated into a date format. The strings 'date' should be replaced by 'time'.</p>

<p>This bug is visible when trying to test a time input with Zend_Date::isValid(), for example:
Zend_Date::isDate('16:00', Zend_Date::TIME_SHORT)
returns false, should return true.</p>

